The paper discusses the security of key extraction protocols that rely on physical characteristics of the communication channel, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of wireless communication and signal strength measurement suggests a possible connection to mobile computing (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The methodology proposed in the paper also involves the use of hidden Markov models, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
